{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_012FRvtJg6z7U8WpDhXixwgR","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_01PwKcp1aT9TW4LWysibLL7G","name":"Write","input":{"file_path":"/tmp/plan.md","content":"# CockroachDB Minor-Version Upgrade — Change Plan\n\n**Cluster:** `crdb-cluster` (namespace `cockroachdb`)\n**Current version:** v24.1.0\n**Target version:** v24.2.x (next minor release)\n**Plan date:** 2026-06-24\n**Status:** REVIEW ONLY — do not execute until approved\n\n---\n\n## 1. Current Cluster Inventory\n\n### 1.1 Topology\n\n| Pod | Node | IP | Status |\n|---|---|---|---|\n| crdb-cluster-0 | karma-2-control-plane | 10.244.0.194 | Running |\n| crdb-cluster-1 | karma-2-control-plane | 10.244.0.195 | Running |\n| crdb-cluster-2 | karma-2-control-plane | 10.244.0.196 | Running |\n\n- **Replicas:** 3 (StatefulSet `crdb-cluster`)\n- **Pod management policy:** `Parallel`\n- **Update strategy:** `RollingUpdate` (partition=0)\n- **Container image:** `cockroachdb/cockroach:v24.1.0`\n- **Security mode:** insecure (`--insecure`)\n\n### 1.2 Container Resources\n\n| Resource | Request | Limit |\n|---|---|---|\n| CPU | 1 core | 1 core |\n| Memory | 2 Gi | 2 Gi |\n\n- `--cache=25%` → ~512 MiB per node\n- `--max-sql-memory=25%` → ~512 MiB per node\n\n### 1.3 Persistent Storage\n\n| PVC | Capacity | StorageClass | Access Mode |\n|---|---|---|---|\n| datadir-crdb-cluster-0 | 10 Gi | standard | ReadWriteOnce |\n| datadir-crdb-cluster-1 | 10 Gi | standard | ReadWriteOnce |\n| datadir-crdb-cluster-2 | 10 Gi | standard | ReadWriteOnce |\n\nPVC retain policy: `Retain` (on deletion and on scale-down).\n\n### 1.4 Services\n\n| Service | Type | Cluster IP | Ports |\n|---|---|---|---|\n| crdb-cluster | ClusterIP (headless) | None | 26257/TCP, 8080/TCP |\n| crdb-cluster-public | ClusterIP | 10.96.9.182 | 26257/TCP, 8080/TCP |\n\n### 1.5 Non-Default Cluster Settings\n\nThe following settings have been explicitly changed from their factory defaults:\n\n| Variable | Current Value | Default Value | Notes |\n|---|---|---|---|\n| `kv.snapshot_rebalance.max_rate` | 1.0 MiB | 32 MiB | Deliberately throttled — rebalance I/O cap |\n| `diagnostics.reporting.enabled` | true | false | Telemetry explicitly enabled |\n| `cluster.secret` | ec3f19e6-… | (empty) | Auto-generated per-cluster; not user-set |\n| `version` | 24.1 | — | Cluster version finalization marker |\n\n### 1.6 Zone Configurations\n\nAll zones share `range_min_bytes = 134217728` (128 MiB) and `range_max_bytes = 536870912` (512 MiB).\n\n| Target | num_replicas | gc.ttlseconds | Notes |\n|---|---|---|---|\n| `RANGE default` | 3 | 14400 (4 h) | Baseline for user data |\n| `DATABASE system` | 5 | 14400 (4 h) | Higher replica target |\n| `RANGE liveness` | 5 | 600 (10 min) | Short GC for liveness range |\n| `RANGE meta` | 5 | 3600 (1 h) | Higher replica target |\n| `RANGE system` | 5 | 14400 (4 h) | Higher replica target |\n| `TABLE system.public.lease` | (inherited) | 600 (10 min) | — |\n| `TABLE system.public.replication_constraint_stats` | (inherited) | 600 (10 min) | — |\n| `TABLE system.public.replication_stats` | (inherited) | 600 (10 min) | — |\n| `TABLE system.public.span_stats_tenant_boundaries` | (inherited) | 3600 (1 h) | — |\n| `TABLE system.public.statement_activity` | (inherited) | 3600 (1 h) | — |\n| `TABLE system.public.statement_statistics` | (inherited) | 3600 (1 h) | — |\n| `TABLE system.public.tenant_usage` | (inherited) | 7200 (2 h) | — |\n| `TABLE system.public.transaction_activity` | (inherited) | 3600 (1 h) | — |\n| `TABLE system.public.transaction_statistics` | (inherited) | 3600 (1 h) | — |\n\n**Configuration mismatch to note:** `num_replicas = 5` is set for several critical\nranges, but the cluster has only 3 nodes. CockroachDB will cap actual replica\nplacement at 3. This pre-exists the upgrade and is not introduced by it.\n\n---\n\n## 2. Pre-Upgrade Checklist\n\nThe following checks must pass before the change window opens.\n\n### 2.1 Cluster Health Gate\n\n```bash\n# All nodes healthy\nkubectl -n cockroachdb exec crdb-cluster-0 -- ./cockroach node status --insecure\n\n# No under-replicated or unavailable ranges\nkubectl -n cockroachdb exec crdb-cluster-0 -- ./cockroach sql --insecure \\\n  -e \"SELECT count(*) FROM crdb_internal.ranges_no_leases\n       WHERE array_length(replicas, 1) < num_replicas;\"\n\n# No active jobs that could conflict\nkubectl -n cockroachdb exec crdb-cluster-0 -- ./cockroach sql --insecure \\\n  -e \"SHOW JOBS;\" | grep -E \"running|pending\"\n```\n\nAll checks must return clean (zero unavailable/under-replicated ranges, no\nlong-running blocking jobs) before proceeding.\n\n### 2.2 Backup Verification\n\nConfirm a recent backup exists (or take one if the environment supports it).\nThe cluster currently has no user databases (only `defaultdb`, `postgres`,\n`system`) so backup scope is limited to cluster-level configuration. Capture\nthe current configuration snapshot for rollback reference:\n\n```bash\n# Snapshot current non-default cluster settings\nkubectl -n cockroachdb exec crdb-cluster-0 -- ./cockroach sql --insecure \\\n  -e \"SELECT variable, value FROM crdb_internal.cluster_settings\n       WHERE value != default_value;\"\n\n# Snapshot current zone configs\nkubectl -n cockroachdb exec crdb-cluster-0 -- ./cockroach sql --insecure \\\n  -e \"SELECT target, raw_config_sql FROM crdb_internal.zones;\"\n```\n\nSave outputs to a durable location before the window begins.\n\n### 2.3 Version Compatibility Confirmation\n\n- Verify `cockroachdb/cockroach:v24.2.x` image is available and pulled to\n  cluster nodes before the window (avoids pull timeout during rollout):\n\n```bash\n# Pre-pull on each node (or let the DaemonSet warm up the image cache)\ndocker pull cockroachdb/cockroach:v24.2.x\n```\n\n- Review CockroachDB 24.2 release notes for deprecations, renamed settings,\n  or removed SQL syntax that may affect current workloads.\n\n### 2.4 `terminationGracePeriodSeconds` Assessment\n\nThe current value is **10 seconds**. This is very short for a graceful drain on\na loaded node. Consider increasing to `60` seconds before the maintenance window\nto allow in-flight transactions to commit cleanly on pod shutdown. If the\ncluster is lightly loaded (as it appears now) 10 s may be sufficient.\n\n---\n\n## 3. What Changes During the Upgrade\n\n### 3.1 Image Update (the only required change)\n\nThe single mechanical change is patching the StatefulSet container image:\n\n```\nFROM: cockroachdb/cockroach:v24.1.0\nTO:   cockroachdb/cockroach:v24.2.x   (pin to a specific patch, e.g. v24.2.3)\n```\n\nThis triggers a rolling replacement of all pods in the StatefulSet, one pod at\na time (update strategy `RollingUpdate`, partition=0).\n\nNo other StatefulSet fields change: replica count, resources, volumes, probes,\ncommand flags, and service accounts remain exactly as they are today.\n\n### 3.2 Cluster Settings — No Changes Required\n\nAll custom settings survive an image-only upgrade unchanged:\n\n| Setting | Action |\n|---|---|\n| `kv.snapshot_rebalance.max_rate = 1.0 MiB` | **Preserve as-is.** The throttle prevents rebalance storms during rolling restarts. |\n| `diagnostics.reporting.enabled = true` | **Preserve as-is.** No impact on upgrade. |\n| `cluster.secret` | **Preserve as-is.** Auto-managed; not touched. |\n\n### 3.3 Zone Configurations — No Changes Required\n\nAll zone configs are stored in the `system` database and persist across the\nupgrade. No SQL re-application is needed.\n\n### 3.4 Version Finalization (required post-upgrade SQL step)\n\nAfter all three pods are running the new binary, the cluster version must be\nfinalized. This is a one-way, irreversible operation:\n\n```sql\nSET CLUSTER SETTING version = crdb_internal.node_executable_version();\n```\n\nThis unlocks 24.2 features and permanently closes the rollback window.\n**Do not run this until all pods have successfully joined on the new binary.**\n\n---\n\n## 4. Upgrade Procedure\n\n### Step 1 — Record baseline state\n\n```bash\nkubectl -n cockroachdb exec crdb-cluster-0 -- ./cockroach node status --insecure\nkubectl -n cockroachdb exec crdb-cluster-0 -- ./cockroach sql --insecure \\\n  -e \"SHOW CLUSTER SETTING version;\"\n```\n\n### Step 2 — Patch the StatefulSet image\n\n```bash\nkubectl -n cockroachdb set image statefulset/crdb-cluster \\\n  db=cockroachdb/cockroach:v24.2.x\n```\n\nThe rolling update replaces pods sequentially. With `Parallel` pod management\nthe StatefulSet controller still updates one pod at a time during a rolling\nupdate. Monitor progress:\n\n```bash\nkubectl -n cockroachdb rollout status statefulset/crdb-cluster --timeout=10m\n```\n\n### Step 3 — Verify each pod on the new binary\n\n```bash\nfor pod in crdb-cluster-0 crdb-cluster-1 crdb-cluster-2; do\n  echo -n \"$pod: \"\n  kubectl -n cockroachdb exec $pod -- ./cockroach version | grep \"Build Tag\"\ndone\n```\n\nAll three must report `v24.2.x` before proceeding.\n\n### Step 4 — Confirm cluster health\n\n```bash\nkubectl -n cockroachdb exec crdb-cluster-0 -- ./cockroach node status --insecure\n```\n\nAll nodes must show `is_live=true` and `is_available=true`.\n\n### Step 5 — Finalize cluster version\n\n```bash\nkubectl -n cockroachdb exec crdb-cluster-0 -- ./cockroach sql --insecure \\\n  -e \"SET CLUSTER SETTING version = crdb_internal.node_executable_version();\"\n```\n\n### Step 6 — Post-upgrade validation\n\n```bash\n# Confirm version finalized\nkubectl -n cockroachdb exec crdb-cluster-0 -- ./cockroach sql --insecure \\\n  -e \"SHOW CLUSTER SETTING version;\"\n\n# Confirm custom settings intact\nkubectl -n cockroachdb exec crdb-cluster-0 -- ./cockroach sql --insecure \\\n  -e \"SELECT variable, value FROM crdb_internal.cluster_settings\n       WHERE value != default_value;\"\n\n# Confirm zone configs intact\nkubectl -n cockroachdb exec crdb-cluster-0 -- ./cockroach sql --insecure \\\n  -e \"SELECT target, raw_config_sql FROM crdb_internal.zones;\"\n\n# Confirm no under-replicated ranges\nkubectl -n cockroachdb exec crdb-cluster-0 -- ./cockroach sql --insecure \\\n  -e \"SELECT count(*) FROM crdb_internal.ranges_no_leases\n       WHERE array_length(replicas, 1) < num_replicas;\"\n```\n\n---\n\n## 5. Rollback Plan\n\nThe rollback window is **before Step 5** (version finalization). Once the\ncluster version is finalized to 24.2, downgrade to 24.1 is not supported by\nCockroachDB.\n\n### If a pod fails to come up on the new binary (before finalization):\n\n```bash\n# Revert image\nkubectl -n cockroachdb set image statefulset/crdb-cluster \\\n  db=cockroachdb/cockroach:v24.1.0\n\nkubectl -n cockroachdb rollout status statefulset/crdb-cluster --timeout=10m\n```\n\nNodes that already restarted on 24.2 will roll back to 24.1. The cluster\nversion setting remains at `24.1` until finalized, so a mixed-version cluster\nduring rollback is safe.\n\n### If the rollout is healthy but there is a post-upgrade problem (before finalization):\n\nSame image revert as above. Re-apply any temporarily adjusted settings if\nthey were modified during the window.\n\n### After finalization:\n\nNo automated rollback is possible. Recovery must follow CockroachDB's disaster\nrecovery procedures for the 24.2 branch.\n\n---\n\n## 6. Risk Register\n\n| Risk | Likelihood | Impact | Mitigation |\n|---|---|---|---|\n| Pod fails readiness probe after image update | Low | Medium | Rollout pauses automatically; investigate logs; rollback if needed |\n| Rebalancing spike causes latency during rolling restart | Low | Medium | `kv.snapshot_rebalance.max_rate = 1.0 MiB` already throttles this |\n| 10 s grace period too short for in-flight transactions | Low | Low | Cluster currently idle; monitor; increase grace period pre-window if load increases |\n| 5-replica zone configs remain under-replicated (pre-existing) | Certain | Low | Pre-existing mismatch; does not worsen with upgrade; consider reducing to 3 post-upgrade if desired |\n| Version finalization is irreversible | Certain | — | Only execute Step 5 after confirming all pods are healthy on 24.2 |\n| Insecure mode (`--insecure`) | Certain | High (security) | Pre-existing; outside scope of this upgrade; track separately |\n\n---\n\n## 7. Approvals Required\n\n- [ ] Database administrator\n- [ ] Platform/SRE lead\n- [ ] Change advisory board (if required by change management policy)\n\n---\n\n*This document is for review only. No changes have been applied to the live cluster.*\n"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1557,"cache_read_input_tokens":35539,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":1557},"output_tokens":8,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"2c7fa004-c150-4db4-8fae-bfb316c3e6c6","uuid":"06f206b5-48b4-4882-b50d-84e52895511c","request_id":"req_011CcMNq1FhZp4Q2aM88krJr"}
